OL,3,CA look at some of the towns hoping to
OL,4,Cbecome UK Town of Culture 2028
OL,6,FThis Scottish Borders town has a
OL,7,Fpopulation of over 10,000 people, and
OL,8,Fboasts a long history in the textile
OL,9,Ftrade.
OL,11,FSurrounded by rolling hills and
OL,12,Fsituated near the River Tweed, the
OL,13,Ftown is 'protected' by an ancient
OL,14,Fearthwork - the Pict's Ditch, or
OL,15,FCatrail.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G13/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35514
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1775153467
OL,3,CA look at some of the towns hoping to
OL,4,Cbecome UK Town of Culture 2028
OL,6,FThe Catrail is essentially a long
OL,7,Fditch with an embankment, around 3-4
OL,8,Fmetres wide and about 1.5 meters deep.
OL,9,FIt stretches nearly 10 miles through
OL,10,Fthe Borders, but no-one is quite sure
OL,11,Fwhy the ancient landmark was erected
OL,12,Fin the first place.
OL,14,FIn slightly more recent history,
OL,15,FRobert Burns penned two poems about
OL,16,FGalashiels: 'Sae Fair Her Hair' and
OL,17,F'Braw Lads', the latter of which is
OL,18,Fsung by some of the townsfolk each
OL,19,Fyear at the 'Braw Lads Gathering'.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G14/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
